    App / Events

    Listing

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/events?months[]=01&years[]=1970&limit=10&offset=0" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/events"
);

let params = {
    "months[]": "01",
    "years[]": "1970",
    "limit": "10",
    "offset": "0",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    GET api/v1/app/events

    Query Parameters

    Parameter Status Description

    years[0] required date array.
    limit required integer.
    offset required integer.

    Create API

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/players-sensors-sessions/create" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"right_foot_file":"ducimus","left_foot_file":"doloribus"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/players-sensors-sessions/create"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "right_foot_file": "ducimus",
    "left_foot_file": "doloribus"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/app/verify-user

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    country_code string required
    phone string required eg: +923361227406, it should be a valid number
    device_type string required options: ios, android
    verification_code string required Required Verification code
    imei string required Required if device type is android
    udid string required Required if device type is ios
    onesignal_token string optional

    Auto Login

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/auto-login" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"device_type":"quaerat","imei":"et","udid":"quia","device_token":"molestias","onesignal_token":"occaecati"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/auto-login"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "device_type": "quaerat",
    "imei": "et",
    "udid": "quia",
    "device_token": "molestias",
    "onesignal_token": "occaecati"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/app/auto-login

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    device_type string required options: ios, android
    imei string required Required if device type is android
    udid string required Required if device type is ios
    device_token string optional
    onesignal_token string optional

    Send Code

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/send-code" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"phone":"occaecati"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/send-code"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "phone": "occaecati"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "A One-Time password has been sent to your phone",
    "Result": {}
}

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/app/send-code

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    phone required optional

    Logout

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/logout" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"device_identifier":"asperiores"}'

    Assignment & Exercise Api's

    Get Exercise Categories


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-exercise-categories?type_id=temporibus" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-exercise-categories"
);

let params = {
    "type_id": "temporibus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Records found successfully!",
    "Result": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "name": "cat1",
            "description": "sdfsdf",
            "image": null
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "name": "cat 2",
            "description": "loremipsum",
            "image": null
        }
    ]
}

    Get Previous Result


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-previous-result?exercise_id=dignissimos" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-previous-result"
);

let params = {
    "exercise_id": "dignissimos",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Success",
    "Result": [
        {
            "date": "2021-06-21 10:07:00",

            "index": "First",
            "value": "First"

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/app/end-exercise

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    player_exercise_id string required you will get this id from start exercise response which is named by id
    scores string required scores is a array of objects containing skill_id,score eg: [{skill_id:1,score:20},{skill_id:2,score:23}]
    completion_time float required
    thumbnail image required
    video_file video required
    version string optional optional

    Perform exercise


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/perform-exercise" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"assignment_id":"voluptatem","exercise_id":"rem","level_id":"ab","scores":"voluptas","started_time":4377.93922,"end_time":207.95801998,"completion_time":21179.2,"thumbnail":"fugit","video_file":"et","version":"nulla","json_data":"quas"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/perform-exercise"

let headers = {

    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "assignment_id": "voluptatem",
    "exercise_id": "rem",
    "level_id": "ab",
    "scores": "voluptas",
    "started_time": 4377.93922,
    "end_time": 207.95801998,
    "completion_time": 21179.2,
    "thumbnail": "fugit",
    "video_file": "et",
    "version": "nulla",
    "json_data": "quas"
}

    method: "POST",

    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/app/perform-exercise

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    assignment_id string optional optional it is required only when you perform exercise from assignments
    exercise_id string required
    level_id string required
    scores string required scores is a array of objects containing skill_id, score eg: [{skill_id:1, score:20}]
    started_time float required
    end_time float required
    completion_time float required
    thumbnail image required
    video_file video required
    version string optional optional
    json_data video required

    Remove Assignments


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/remove-assignments" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/remove-assignments"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Player assignment deleted successfully",
    "Result": []
}

    HTTP Request

    GET api/v1/app/remove-assignments

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Status Description
    player_assignment_id required integer

    Complete Assignment


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/complete-assignment" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"assignment_id":"magni"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/complete-assignment"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "assignment_id": "magni"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Assignment completed",
    "Result": {}
}

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/app/complete-assignment

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    assignment_id string required

    POST api/v1/app/battle/create-match

    exercise_id[] optional optional (when select exercises make sure you select exercises for all rounds)

    user_ids[] required optional
    date (optional) optional
    time (optional) optional
    title (optional) optional

    Contact Api


    Requires authentication You can store contacts and you need his/her id from users table

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/contact/store?contact_user_id=illum" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/contact/store"
);

let params = {
    "contact_user_id": "illum",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 202,
    "Message": "Record has been saved",
    "Result": {
        "user_id": 2,
        "contact_user_id": "1",
        "updated_at": "2020-06-29 08:12:16",
        "created_at": "2020-06-29 08:12:16",
        "id": 2
    }
}

    Example response (401):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 401,
    "Message": "Contact UserID can't be added again. It's already defined in database.",
    "Result": {}
}

    Example response (401):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 401,
    "Message": {
        "contact_user_id": [
            "The selected contact user id is invalid."
        ]
    },
    "Result": {}
}

    Example response (401):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 401,
    "Message": "contact_user_id field is empty or not set",
    "Result": {}
}

    POST api/v1/app/contact/store

    Parameter Status Description

    time h:i optional

    line string required
    position string required
    players array optional optional

    api/v1/dashboard/battle/get-round-result


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/battle/get-round-result?battle_id=deleniti&round=consequatur" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/battle/get-round-result"
);

let params = {
    "battle_id": "deleniti",
    "round": "consequatur",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,

    UpdatesTrainerProfile


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/profile/update-profile" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"first_name":"qui","last_name":"iste","middle_name":"qui","surname":"amet","email":"doloremque","phone":"non","nationality_id":"inventore","jersey_number":"distinctio","profile_picture":"dolor"}'

    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/profile/update-profile"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "first_name": "qui",
    "last_name": "iste",
    "middle_name": "qui",
    "surname": "amet",
    "email": "doloremque",
    "phone": "non",
    "nationality_id": "inventore",
    "jersey_number": "distinctio",
    "profile_picture": "dolor"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Resend setup password link

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/auth/resend-setup-password-link?token=e6a4015b948dcd299e7b27ae8f95921f" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/auth/resend-setup-password-link"
);

let params = {
    "token": "e6a4015b948dcd299e7b27ae8f95921f",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v4/dashboard/events/create

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    clubId integer required .
    type string required options: training, assignment, match or event .
    categoryId integer required .
    title string required min 1 chars max 100 chars .
    start date required date format eg: 2021-04-10 19:00:00 .
    end date required date format eg: 2021-04-12 23:00:00 .
    repetitionId integer required .
    location string required .
    latitude string required .
    longitude string required .
    teamId integer required .
    linesId[0] array required integer .
    positionsId[0] array required integer .
    playersId[0] array required integer .
    details string optional optional .
    eventTypeId integer optional optional if type can "training" then this key will required .
    assignmentId integer optional optional if type can "assignment" then this key will required .
    opponentTeamId integer optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentLinesId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentPositionsId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentPlayersId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    playingAreaId integer optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .

    categoryId integer required .
    title string required min 1 chars max 100 chars .
    start date required date format eg: 2021-04-10 19:00:00 .
    end date required date format eg: 2021-04-12 23:00:00 .
    currentStartDate date required date format eg: 2021-04-12 23:00:00 .
    currentEndDate date required date format eg: 2021-04-12 23:00:00 .
    repetitionId integer required .
    location string required .
    latitude string required .
    longitude string required .
    teamId integer required .
    linesId[0] array required integer .
    positionsId[0] array required integer .
    playersId[0] array required integer .
    details string optional optional .
    eventTypeId integer optional optional if type can "training" then this key will required .
    assignmentId integer optional optional if type can "assignment" then this key will required .
    opponentTeamId integer optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentLinesId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentPositionsId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentPlayersId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    playingAreaId integer optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .

    Delete

    Example request:

    curl -X DELETE \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/events/delete/1?actionType=single&start=2021-04-10+19%3A00%3A00&end=2021-04-10+19%3A00%3A00&groupId=1234567&clubId=1" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/events/delete/1"
);

let params = {
    "actionType": "single",
    "start": "2021-04-10 19:00:00",
    "end": "2021-04-10 19:00:00",
    "groupId": "1234567",
    "clubId": "1",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "DELETE",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    -d '{"firstName":"Shahzaib","lastName":"Parent","countryCode":92,"phoneNo":1234567890,"image":"est"}'

    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/auth/profile/setup"
);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",

};

    Verify otp for updating email

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/auth/profile/update/verify-otp" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"otp":123456}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/auth/profile/update/verify-otp"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "otp": 123456
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Your otp code has verified successfully",
    "Result": {}
}

    Example response (422):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 422,
    "Message": "Invalid Parameters",
    "Result": {
        "otp": [
            "The otp must be a valid otp."
        ]
    }
}

    Example response (404):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 404,
    "Message": "Invalid otp",
    "Result": {}
}

    Example response (500):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 500,

    -d '{"currentPassword":"123456789","newPassword":"123456789","confirmPassword":"123456789","deviceType":"web","deviceToken":"dfnfsdnADBKFBSuhsd&&#@$jhksd","ip":"203.101.189.100","macId":"10:3b:b0:53:39:a7"}'

}

    method: "POST",

    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/clubs/trainers"
);

let params = {
    "clubId": "1",
    "limit": "10",
    "offset": "0",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Delete team trainer

    Example request:

    curl -X DELETE \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/clubs/trainers/teams/1/delete/1?clubId=1" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v4/dashboard/clubs/trainers/teams/1/delete/1"
);

let params = {
    "clubId": "1",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "DELETE",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

};

    "team_id": 20,
    "line": [],
    "position": [],
    "player_id": [],
    "metric_type": "expedita",
    "kick_strength": 5,
    "max_speed": 20,
    "leg_distribution": "earum",
    "ball_kicks": 10,
    "total_distance": 18,
    "impact": 9
}

    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,

    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    GET api/v1/app/get-data

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Status Description
    countries optional optional value To get the countries, value should be 'get'
    customary_foots optional optional value To get the customary_foots, value should be 'get'
    positions optional optional value To get the positions, value should be 'get'

    Home

    APIs for home feeds

    api/v1/app/home/feeds

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/home/feeds" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/home/feeds"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 401,
    "Message": "Unauthenticated user to access this route",
    "Result": {}
}

    HTTP Request

    GET api/v1/app/home/feeds

    Single Feed

    Getting single feed brief details with comments and likes

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/home/single-feed?post_id=quaerat" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/home/single-feed"
);

let params = {
    "post_id": "quaerat",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Parent Sharing / Players

    Listing

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/parent-sharing/players?limit=10&offset=0" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/parent-sharing/players"
);

let params = {
    "limit": "10",

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \

    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"

    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/parent-sharing/auth/profile/update/resend-otp"

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/parent-sharing/auth/profile/update/resend-otp

    Update password

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/parent-sharing/auth/profile/update/password" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"currentPassword":"123456789","newPassword":"123456789","confirmPassword":"123456789","deviceType":"web","deviceToken":"dfnfsdnADBKFBSuhsd&&#@$jhksd","ip":"203.101.189.100","macId":"10:3b:b0:53:39:a7"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/parent-sharing/auth/profile/update/password"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "currentPassword": "123456789",
    "newPassword": "123456789",
    "confirmPassword": "123456789",
    "deviceType": "web",
    "deviceToken": "dfnfsdnADBKFBSuhsd&&#@$jhksd",
    "ip": "203.101.189.100",
    "macId": "10:3b:b0:53:39:a7"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Password has updated successfully",

    Update folllow request status


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/update-follow-request-status" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"user_id":"velit","status":"quo"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/update-follow-request-status"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "user_id": "velit",
    "status": "quo"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Search Teams


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/search-teams?keyword=quo" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/search-teams"
);

let params = {
    "keyword": "quo",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Teams found",
    "Result": [
        {
            "id": 2,
            "team_name": "Ajax U16",

            "description": "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book.     reviewTrainer


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/review-trainer" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"trainer_id":"enim","rating":"sunt","review":"excepturi"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/review-trainer"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "trainer_id": "enim",
    "rating": "sunt",
    "review": "excepturi"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/notifications/delete" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"notification_id":"consectetur"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/notifications/delete"
);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

    "notification_id": "consectetur"
}

    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})

    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Update User Privacy Setting


    Requires authentication updating user privacy setting, we need user_privacy_setting id from user_privacy_settings table, access_modifier id from access_modifiers table and user_id which must be matched to current auth user id

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/update-user-privacy-setting?user_id=voluptatem&user_privacy_setting_id=illo&access_modifier_id=doloribus" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/update-user-privacy-setting"
);

let params = {
    "user_id": "voluptatem",
    "user_privacy_setting_id": "illo",
    "access_modifier_id": "doloribus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Sensor Module

    Get File

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-file?version_number=minus" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-file"
);

let params = {
    "version_number": "minus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Note - Response (200):

    
                The endpoint for the S3 Bucket object is in the response attribute, "Result".

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Download Link Provided",
    "Result": "https:\/\/jogobucket-1.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com\/sensor_module\/test.zip?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD&X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=AKIAW2RPSZR2OFELRRU2%2F20211118%2Feu-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20211118T075123Z&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Expires=600&X-Amz-Signature=a4dc83cd559bbee10c06ef5f0a6a06f8fdec23254cb7afc193453e6a2326b6ab"
}

    Post Sensor Detail

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/post-sensor-detail" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"version_number":"sed","file":"quia"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/post-sensor-detail"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "version_number": "sed",
    "file": "quia"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Successful",
    "Result": {}
}

);

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/exercises/play-exercise-video?player_id=possimus&exercise_id=corrupti" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \

    Get Filters


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/players/get-filters" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"team_id":"ab"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/players/get-filters"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "team_id": "ab"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Player Exercise Listing


    Requires authentication Getting player exercises data in which we will be getting done exercises details.

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/players/player-exercises-listing?player_id=laborum&assignment_id=ea" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/players/player-exercises-listing"
);

let params = {
    "player_id": "laborum",
    "assignment_id": "ea",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Get Statistics Top Records


    Requires authentication

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/players/statistics/top-records" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"player_id":"inventore","from":"ipsam","to":"ut"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/dashboard/players/statistics/top-records"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "player_id": "inventore",
    "from": "ipsam",
    "to": "ut"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    POST api/v1/trainerapp/events/create

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    clubId integer required .
    type string required options: training, assignment, match or event .
    categoryId integer required .
    title string required min 1 chars max 100 chars .
    start date required date format eg: 2021-04-10 19:00:00 .
    end date required date format eg: 2021-04-12 23:00:00 .
    repetitionId integer required .
    location string required .
    latitude string required .
    longitude string required .
    teamId integer required .
    positionsId[0] array required integer .
    playersId[0] array required integer .
    details string optional optional .
    eventTypeId integer optional optional if type can "training" then this key will required .
    assignmentId integer optional optional if type can "assignment" then this key will required .
    opponentTeamId integer optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentPositionsId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    opponentPlayersId[0] array optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .
    playingAreaId integer optional optional if type can "match" then this key will required .

    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"player_ids":[],"exercise_id":2,"level_id":6}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/exercises/trainer-session-create"
);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "player_ids": [],
    "exercise_id": 2,
    "level_id": 6
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    POST api/v1/trainerapp/exercises/trainer-session-start

    Body Parameters

    Parameter Type Status Description
    player_id integer optional it will be sent if exercise is to be repeated
    session_id integer required

    HTTP Request

    Get Assignments

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/assignments?clubId=voluptatem" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/assignments"
);

let params = {
    "clubId": "voluptatem",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/assignments/get-player-assignment-details"
);

let params = {
    "player_id": "aspernatur",
    "assignment_id": "veniam",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

);

    Get Trainer Profile

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/get-trainer-profile?trainer_id=est&club_id=vitae" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/get-trainer-profile"
);

let params = {
    "trainer_id": "est",
    "club_id": "vitae",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    GET api/v1/trainerapp/get-trainer-profile

    Query Parameters

    Parameter Status Description
    trainer_id required
    club_id optional integer

    GetTeamPlayers

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/get-team-players?team_id=vel&limit=rem&page=20" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/get-team-players"
);

let params = {
    "team_id": "vel",
    "limit": "rem",
    "page": "20",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    HTTP Request

    GET api/v1/trainerapp/settings/get-team-details

    Query Parameters

    Parameter Status Description
    team_id required integer

    AcceptTeamRequest

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/settings/accept-team-request" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"request_id":18}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/trainerapp/settings/accept-team-request"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "request_id": 18
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Example response (200):

    {
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Request Accepted",
    "Result": {}
}

    Update Profile

    Example request:

    curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/update-profile" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"first_name":"amet","last_name":"aliquam","date_of_birth":"aut","nationality_id":2,"customary_foot_id":12,"positionsId":[],"height":5739.07,"weight":311.1,"jersey_number":"ipsam","profile_picture":"et","cover_photo":"aperiam"}'

    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/update-profile"
);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",

    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

    "jersey_number": "ipsam",

    "cover_photo": "aperiam"

    method: "POST",

    body: body

    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Fetch Single Story


    Requires authentication Getting story of the current player

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/stories/show?story_id=aut" \

    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/stories/show"
);

let params = {
    "story_id": "aut",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));

    Search Clubs

    Example request:

    curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/search-clubs?keyword=molestiae" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
    const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/search-clubs"
);

let params = {
    "keyword": "molestiae",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
